-- Fitch to Cut Hungary Sovereign Credit by Two Steps to Junk, Origo Reports
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2011-12-21T17:12:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/fitch-to-cut-hungary-sovereign-credit-by-two-steps-to-junk-origo-reports.html
Fitch Ratings has notified the
Hungarian government of its intention to cut the country’s
sovereign credit grade by two steps to junk, Origo news website
reported, citing two “market sources independent of each
other.”  Hungary is currently rated BBB-, the lowest investment
grade, with a negative outlook at Fitch.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  